   <abstract>Plat and survey of county border between Wilson and Cannon counties. Indicated are the Cumberland River, various roads, Coles ferry, Batotes ferry, paper mill, Lebanon, Statesville, and Milton. Survey points noted are the former corner of Wilson and Smith counties, the former corner of Warren and Rutherford counties, and the Ridge between the waters of Stones River and Caney Fork River.</abstract>
   <abstract>Thomas Anderson, surveyor of Sumner County, drew this map to ascertain the boundary between WIlson and the newly created Cannon counties in 1836. Anderson, unpaid by 1837, petitioned the state legislature for compensation for surveying the line and drawing this map. (RG 60: Petitions, 1837-88)</abstract>
